703669f-a.text:
Clinton Street, west side, between State Street and Atlantic Ave, showing lot where once stood the United States Apartments, Brooklyn's first large apartment house. Also seen is State Street, west of Clinton Street,
showing rear views of houses on south side.
April 29, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
703669f-a.folder: Clinton Street & State Street, Brooklyn, NY

706861f-a.text:
(1)
111-121 State Street, north side, between Clinton Street (right), and Sidney Plaoe, as s een across clearing upon which once stood the U.S. Apartments The corner building has no numerical designation.
April 29, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
(2)
The same, a more limited view of No. 1, showing also the rears of the south side of State Street. Also shown, is the cleared site upon which stood the U.S. Apartments, on the west side of Clinton Street, between Atlantic Ave., and State Street.
April 29, 1935.
P. L. Sperr.
